BROWN beef; drain. Stir in water and seasoning mix. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture is thickened. SPREAD 2 tablespoons beans over each tostada shell. Top with 1/2 cup meat mixture and 1/4 cup cheese. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with desired toppings.